		"body": "Fixes: #14386 \r\n\r\n**Problem**\r\n\r\nWhen Joplin’s internal dark theme is enabled, the native title bar and scroll bar on Windows remains white. This creates a visual inconsistency and breaks the expected dark appearance of the application from a user’s perspective.\r\n\r\n**Solution**\r\nThis PR synchronizes the title bar with Joplin’s internal theme by applying Electron’s nativeTheme.themeSource directly in app.ts.\r\nWhenever the user changes the theme or toggles themeAutoDetect, the native title bar is updated to match the selected theme (Light, Dark, or OLED Dark). If auto-detect is enabled, the system preference continues to be respected.\r\n\r\n**Test Plan**\r\n- Build and run Joplin locally on Windows/macOS\r\n- Switch between Light, Dark, and OLED Dark themes\r\n- Enable and disable themeAutoDetect\r\n- Verify that the native title bar updates correctly in all cases and stays in sync with the active theme\r\n\r\n**AI disclosure:**\r\nI used AI as a support tool to better understand Electron’s native theme APIs and to help structure the overall code architecture, ensuring the new logic integrates cleanly without relying on IPC and without breaking the existing auto-detect flow.\r\n\r\nI have reviewed and understood all the changes, compiled the application locally, and tested the fix to confirm it works as intended.\r\n\r\n<!--\r\n\r\nBefore contributing, please read the contribution guidelines: https://github.com/laurent22/joplin/blob/dev/readme/dev/index.md\r\n\r\nIf this is a Google Summer of Code pull request, please read the [GSoC pull request guidelines](https://github.com/joplin/gsoc/blob/master/pull_request_guidelines.md).\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Pull request title**: Please prefix the title with the platform you are targetting.\r\n\r\nHere are some examples of good titles:\r\n\r\n- Desktop: Resolves #123: Added new setting to change font\r\n- Mobile, Desktop: Fixes #456: Fixed config screen error\r\n- All: Resolves #777: Made synchronisation faster\r\n\r\nAnd here's an explanation of the title format:\r\n\r\n- \"Desktop\" for the Windows/macOS/Linux app (Electron app)\r\n- \"Mobile\" for the mobile app (or \"Android\" / \"iOS\" if the pull request only applies to one of the mobile platforms)\r\n- \"CLI\" for the CLI app\r\n\r\nIf it's two platforms, separate them with commas - \"Desktop, Mobile\" or if it's for all platforms, prefix with \"All\".\r\n\r\nIf it's not related to any platform (such as a translation, change to the documentation, etc.), simply don't add a platform.\r\n\r\nThen please append the issue that you've addressed or fixed. Use \"Resolves #123\" for new features or improvements and \"Fixes #123\" for bug fixes.\r\n\r\n-->",
